{
  "texts": [
    "They argued that the solution of VNF placement based on calculations at time t can be inappropriate for time (t+1) where the VNF are effectively placed.",
    "This is due to the resources spinning-up process that can take a long time; thus the physical network state (particularly the physical paths delay) may change meanwhile.",
    "The authors proposed to predict the state at (t+1) so that the placement remains consistent with the requirements.",
    "They used a training vector that captures the parameters affecting the delay: the inference caused by resource sharing on end nodes, the length of link connecting iii) them and the traffic passing through it.",
    "To assess their approach, the authors generated a training dataset using a stochastic modeling for delay analysis of a VoIP network [54]."
  ]
}